text.section:
The Exchange shall be administered in a manner designed to:
prevent discrimination;
streamline enrollment and other processes to minimize expenses and achieve maximum efficiency;
prevent waste, fraud, and abuse; and
promote financial integrity.

section.section:
The fraud, waste, and abuse detection and prevention program shall:
establish a framework for internal controls;
identify control cycles;
conduct risk assessments;
document processes; and
implement controls.

The report shall:
be in the standardized format required by the Secretary;
include data regarding:
health plan participation, ratings, coverage, price, quality improvement measures, and benefits;
consumer choice, participation, and satisfaction information to the extent the information is available;
financial integrity, fee assessments, and status of the Fund; and
any other appropriate metrics related to the operation of the Exchange that may be used to evaluate Exchange performance, assure transparency, and facilitate research and analysis;
include data to identify disparities related to gender, race, ethnicity, geographic location, language, disability, or other attributes of special populations; and
include information on its fraud, waste, and abuse detection and prevention program.
